gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: Land Cover and Land Cover Change in selected hot-spots outside Europe

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString:
The Copernicus Hot Spot Monitoring (HSM) activity delivers land cover and land cover change products on Key Landscapes for Conservation (KLC) and protected areas, with an initial emphasis on the African continent, which are characterized by pronounced anthropogenic pressures that require high mapping accuracy.
Land cover and land cover change products are based on medium to high and very high resolution (from approximately 1 m to 30 m spatial resolution) with a change assessment frequency between 1 to 20 years.
The classification scheme follows the Land Cover Classification System (LCCS) developed by the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations (FAO) .
Data in the related series will be published by the end of March 2023
